      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── Step-by-step manual ────────────────────── -->
<section class="section" style="background: var(--color-surface); border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);" aria-label="Manual setup steps">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="fade-in">
      <div class="section-label">Manual setup</div>
      <h2 class="section-heading">Step by step</h2>
      <p class="section-subheading">
        The one-liner does all of this automatically. But here's what's happening under the hood.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="setup-steps fade-in delay-1">

      <div class="setup-step">
        <div class="setup-step-num">1</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Clone the repo</h3>
          <p>Clone Agent PMO into your code directory.</p>
          <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/MelbourneDeveloper/project_status.git
cd project_status</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="setup-step">
        <div class="setup-step-num">2</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Install .NET SDK</h3>
          <p>The dashboard is an F# script run via <code>dotnet fsi</code>. Install .NET 8+:</p>
          <pre><code># macOS (Homebrew)
brew install dotnet

# Ubuntu / Debian
sudo apt-get update &amp;&amp; sudo apt-get install -y dotnet-sdk-8.0

# Windows (winget)
winget install Microsoft.DotNet.SDK.8

# Or download from: https://dot.net</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="setup-step">
        <div class="setup-step-num">3</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Install and authenticate gh CLI</h3>
          <p>The dashboard fetches PR and CI status via the GitHub CLI.</p>
          <pre><code># macOS
brew install gh

# Ubuntu / Debian
sudo apt install gh

# Windows
winget install GitHub.cli

# Authenticate (all platforms)
gh auth login</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="setup-step">
        <div class="setup-step-num">4</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Run the report manually</h3>
          <p>Verify everything works before setting up the scheduler.</p>
          <pre><code>dotnet fsi dashboard/repo-report.fsx
# Opens dashboard/repo-report.html</code></pre>
          <p>If you see your repos in the report, you're good to go.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="setup-step">
        <div class="setup-step-num">5</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Set up the scheduled refresh</h3>
          <p>The setup script handles this. Manual instructions:</p>
          <pre><code># macOS — launchd (runs every 3 minutes)
cp com.agentpmo.repo-report.plist ~/Library/LaunchAgents/
launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.agentpmo.repo-report.plist

# Linux — cron job
echo "*/3 * * * * cd $(pwd) &amp;&amp; dotnet fsi dashboard/repo-report.fsx" | crontab -

# Windows — Task Scheduler (PowerShell, admin)
# The setup.ps1 script handles this automatically</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="setup-step">
        <div class="setup-step-num">6</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Install the enforcement skill (optional)</h3>
          <p>To standardise your other repos with the Claude skill:</p>
          <pre><code>make install-skill
# Symlinks enforce-repo-standards/ into ~/.claude/skills/</code></pre>
          <p>Then in any repo: tell Claude to run the <strong>enforce-repo-standards</strong> skill.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── Config ────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="section" aria-label="Configuration options">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="fade-in">
      <div class="section-label">Configuration</div>
      <h2 class="section-heading">Tailor it to your setup</h2>
      <p class="section-subheading">
        Copy <code>dashboard/config.example.json</code> to <code>dashboard/config.json</code> to customise.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="fade-in delay-1">
      <pre><code>{
  "scanPaths": [
    "~/Documents/Code",
    "~/Projects"
  ],
  "excludeRepos": [
    "archived-project",
    "vendor"
  ],
  "refreshIntervalSeconds": 180,
  "reportPath": "dashboard/repo-report.html",
  "github": {
    "fetchPRs": true,
    "fetchCI": true,
    "fetchReleases": true
  }
}</code></pre>

      <div class="callout callout-accent">
        <strong>Multiple scan paths supported.</strong> If your repos live in different directories, list them all in <code>scanPaths</code>. The dashboard merges results from all paths.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

